03/04/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Justice Minister Ingrid Anticevic Marinovic opened a three-day seminar on judicial reforms on Wednesday (2 April). 
Specialists and government officials from Southeast European countries are discussing ways to improve policies designed to curb human trafficking. 
Marinovic presented draft amendments to Croatia's penal code, in accordance with international conventions and protocols. 
The country also will harmonise its legislation with clauses in the Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU, referring to accommodation and repatriation of trafficking victims. 
(HINA - 02/04/03)
